entries.boss_detected: pcontrast3 Alliance HQ:  pcontrast1 < Warning! Enemy commander detected on attack vector! pcontrast3 >
entries.complete: Excellent work, Pilot! The Imperial presence in this sector has been soundly beaten. Return to base!
entries.dd_boss_taunt_1: You killed my men. Now you're mine!
entries.dd_boss_taunt_2: If you cut your engines, I promise not to harm you.
entries.dd_boss_taunt_3: I'm going to enjoy spacing you.
entries.dd_boss_taunt_4: A thousand creds to the man who takes him out!
entries.dd_boss_taunt_5: You shouldn't have come here Rebel fool, you won't leave alive!
entries.found_loc: We are uploading coordinates of suspected Imperial ambushes. Investigate and eliminate all hostiles.
entries.level_boss: pcontrast3 Alliance HQ: < ff0000 The Imperials are sending a highly trained %TO after you. Stand by for coordinates... pcontrast3 >
entries.level_boss_dead: Good work, the commander has been destroyed. We're still picking up Imperial activity, however. Stand by...
entries.level_increase: We've detected that more TIE ships have been sent into the sector.
entries.quest_destroy_d: Fly to this potential ambush point. Destroy all enemy craft that come your way.
entries.quest_location_d: Patrol the Tatooine system in search of potential TIE ambushes. The Empire will gather strength in the Tatooine system if we fail!
entries.targets_behind: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer:  < pcontrast1 Enemy targets coming in from behind! pcontrast3 >
entries.targets_detected: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer:  < pcontrast1 Enemy targets on incoming attack vector! pcontrast3 >
entries.taunt_2: Take out that Rebel fool boys.
entries.taunt_3: This is the last time you will get in the way of the Empire!
entries.taunt_4: What is the point of this Rebel, you can't win!
entries.taunt_5: I hope you don't value your life Rebel!
entries.title: Tatooine system: Duty mission: Break up TIE ambushes.
entries.title_d: Break up TIE ambushes. These missions have been outlined to give you some much needed experience in space combat, you can stop when you feel that you have learned enough.
